West Nile virus surveillance 2001 - USA (19) 20010906.2136
West Nile virus, horse - USA (Massachusetts) 20010912.2203
Date: Tue 18 Sep 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: United States Department of Agriculture -APHIS, Emergency
Management Warning 16, 14 Sep 2001 [edited
<http://www.aphis.usda.gov/oa/wnv/wnvemw16.html>

First Horses in Alabama Confirmed with West Nile Virus
------------------------------------------------------
Horses in Dale County, Alabama (2) and in Plymouth County, Massachusetts
(1), have been confirmed as positive for West Nile virus (WNV) infection.
These are the first equine cases of clinical WNV infection ever detected in
Alabama and the first in Massachusetts in 2001 [already reported on
ProMED-mail, see "West Nile virus, horse - USA (Massachusetts)
20010912.2203". - Mod; one equine case of WNV infection was detected in
Massachusetts last year.
The horses in southeast Alabama are stable-mates that became ill in late
August and are recovering. The horse in southeast Massachusetts is a
2-year-old gelding that is recovering from a neurologic illness which began
on 1 Sep 2001.
WNV infection was confirmed in all 3 horses at the National Veterinary
Services Laboratories (NVSL). Each had a WNV-positive IgM-capture
enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) and plaque-reduction
neutralization test on serum.
